constantValues: Biographical information about the education institutions a contact attended or is attending, the areas of study (major/minor) concentrated on, activities and roles served, preferences (football booster, patron of the on-campus art museum, etc.), and the start and end dates associated with this information.  It's particularly important for mid-level and major gift fundraisers based in the United States to understand someone's university/college alumni/alumnae network and peers in order to build a bigger qualified prospect pipeline.  University/college association is not as relevant or important in the UK, for example, compared to the US.  Nonprofit organizations with a bigger focus on major gifts care more about tracking educational information at a deeper level.
